problem: Circle $O$ is located on the coordinate plane with center at $(2,3)$.  One endpoint of a diameter is at $(-1,-1)$.  What are the coordinates of the other endpoint of this diameter?  Express your answer as an ordered pair.
model_solution:
Step 1: Since the center of the circle is at (2,3), and one endpoint of the diameter is at (-1,-1), the midpoint of the diameter is at (2,3).
Step 2: The other endpoint of the diameter is the same distance in the opposite direction from the midpoint as (-1,-1) is from the midpoint, so we add the same horizontal and vertical distances.
Step 3: The horizontal distance from (-1,-1) to (2,3) is 3 units to the right, so the other endpoint is 3 units to the left of (2,3). The vertical distance from (-1,-1) to (2,3) is 4 units up, so the other endpoint is 4 units up from (2,3).
Step 4: The coordinates of the other endpoint of the diameter are $\boxed{(2-3,3+4),}$ which simplifies to $(5,7).$
